                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='17206' id='14' type-v2='text' w='99002' x='499' y='81870'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>Scalability Analysis Insights</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>1. Training runtime increases approximately linearly with dataset size, indicating effective distributed scaling within the Spark environment.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>2. Model performance (AUC ≈ 0.90) remains stable across increasing data volumes, demonstrating that predictive quality does not degrade when scaling training data.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>3. The seconds-per-million-rows efficiency metric remains relatively stable, suggesting that Spark’s distributed execution effectively manages computational workload without significant overhead.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='8'>4. These results indicate that the PySpark ML pipeline is capable of handling significantly larger datasets with predictable computational cost, supporting scalable machine learning deployment.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
